<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFDAD6540D8DF51017B73A6F" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" type="description">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFDAD6540D8DF51017B73A6F" blockId="12.[1991,2586,2611,3034]" lastBlockId="12.[1379,2585,3039,3190]" pageId="12" pageNumber="703">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFDAD6540D8DF51019EE3D0C" bold="true" box="[1991,2241,2812,2837]" pageId="12" pageNumber="703">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 
<quantity id="A7199B0AFFDAD6540330F51018F93D0C" box="[2426,2518,2812,2837]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" unit="mm" value="45.0">45 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity id="A7199B0AFFDAD6540D82F4F719003D25" box="[1992,2095,2843,2876]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" unit="mm" value="43.0">43 mm</quantity>
, ear 9-5-10 mm, hindfoot 
<quantity id="A7199B0AFFDAD65403F6F4F71B3E3D25" box="[2492,2577,2843,2876]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
, forearm 38-40 mm; weight 
<quantity id="A7199B0AFFDAD6540313F4AE18AA3D7A" box="[2393,2437,2882,2915]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="7.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" unit="g" value="7.0">7 g</quantity>
. Newton's Long-fingered Bat has blackish gray dorsal and ventral pelage. There is also a reddish morph, although less abundant. It has narrow hairy edge along dorsal side of wing membrane in area between femur and humerus. Lower part of this membrane has few and sparse hairs, and uropatagium is hairless on both sides. Ears are small, and tragusis relatively long (4: 
<quantity id="A7199B0AFFDAD654037EF3DB18A53A49" box="[2356,2442,3127,3152]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
) and narrow, with rounded tip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="349E6667FFDAD6540A2DF33816E43B92" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419164" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6419164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419164/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" startId="12.[103,133,3284,3309]" targetBox="[11,2761,17,3658]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFDAD6540A2DF33816E43B92" blockId="12.[101,2517,3284,3470]" pageId="12" pageNumber="703">
On following pages: 21. Least Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDAD65408CDF33812263AF4" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[647,777,3284,3309]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Miniopterus</taxonomicName>
minon; 22. Sandy Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDAD6540EE7F33814003AF4" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[1197,1327,3284,3309]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Miniopterus</taxonomicName>
arenarius); 23. African Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDAD6540D48F33816C03AF4" authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="1936" box="[1794,2031,3284,3309]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="704" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanus">Miniopterus africanus</taxonomicName>
); 24. Natal Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDAD6540A24F31710483B0D" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[110,359,3323,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="705" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="natalensis">Miniopterus natalensis</taxonomicName>
); 25. Mozambican Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDAD6540944F317151F3B0D" box="[782,1072,3323,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="703" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mossambicus">Miniopterus mossambicus</taxonomicName>
); 26. Lesser Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDAD6540FDEF31717BB3B0D" authorityName="Thomas &amp; Schwann" authorityYear="1906" box="[1428,1684,3323,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="706" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fraterculus">Miniopterus fraterculus</taxonomicName>
